Lead and manage research focused on developing and applying LLMs for data center lifecycle management, including design, operation, and optimization;
Prototype and validate LLM-driven solutions for improving energy efficiency, predictive maintenance, and operational excellence in data centers;
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including industry partners, to translate research insights into practical applications and deployable technologies;
Publish high-quality research papers in top-tier journals and present findings at leading international conferences;
Supervise and mentor junior researchers, PhD students, and interns in the development of LLM-based models for data center optimization;
Stay updated on the latest advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), and data center technologies, and incorporate them into research projects.
Job Requirements:
PhD in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field, with a focus on AI/ML or data center technologies;
Proven experience in conducting high-impact research in AI, particularly in the application of LLMs or other advanced ML techniques;
Strong publication record in reputable journals and conferences related to AI, ML, and data center operations;
Demonstrated expertise in data center design, operation, energy optimization, or sustainability is highly desirable;
Experience in leading research teams and managing complex research projects;
Excellent programming skills, with proficiency in Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, or other relevant AI/ML frameworks;
Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to translate complex technical concepts into practical applications;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to present complex research findings to both academic and industry audiences.
